# The quality of being [[genial]]
#:''Sometimes this throat uttered Yes, sometimes it uttered No; sometimes it made inquiries about a time worn denizen of the place. Once it surprised her notions by remarking upon the friendliness and '''geniality''' written in the faces of the hills around.'' — Thomas Hardy, ''Return of the Native'', [[s:The Return of the Native/Book 2/Chapter 3|Chapter 3]].